<item>
            <title>[SPARK-40169] Fix the issue with Parquet column index and predicate pushdown in Data source V1</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-40169</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This is a follow for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-39833&quot; title=&quot;Filtered parquet data frame count() and show() produce inconsistent results when spark.sql.parquet.filterPushdown is true&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-39833&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-39833&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. In &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/37419,&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/37419,&lt;/a&gt; we disabled column index for Parquet due to correctness issues that we found when filtering data on the partition column overlapping with data schema.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This ticket is for permanent and thorough fix for the issue and re-enablement of the column index. See more details in the PR linked above.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
